message: Always combine like-sized creatures first (e.g., small with small). Combining two like creatures (e.g., lizard + frog) makes a new creature with value 0. Combining three like creatures (e.g., lizard + frog + bird) generally gives a value of 5. The growth serum is excellent! Use it once on a combined creature to get ~15-25 value, and a second time to get ~25-35 value. The previous player's advice about 'once or twice' for growth serum seems correct, as two uses reliably increased value. Do NOT use the mutation catalyst; it's always negative. The highest value I reached was 35 by combining three small creatures and then applying growth serum twice. Focus on combining 3 creatures of the same size, then apply growth serum twice.

message: Hello! The key to success is careful use of the growth serum. Combining 'like' creatures (same size, same environment) gives a 0-value hybrid. Combining creatures of the same size but different environments (e.g., medium land + medium water) or different sizes (e.g., small air + large land) can give an item with value 5. Always apply the ğŸŒ¡ï¸ growth serum once to any newly formed hybrid, as this consistently increases its value. For most hybrids, applying the ğŸŒ¡ï¸ growth serum a *second* time yields an even higher value (e.g., from 20 to 30 or 25 to 35). However, applying it a *third* time will result in a strongly negative value, so do not overdo it. The ğŸ§¬ mutation catalyst seems to always cause negatives, so avoid using it entirely. Aim for 30-35 points per round by combining creatures and applying the growth serum once or twice to the resulting hybrid.
